javaslang.algebra

Interface HigherKinded8<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,T8,TYPE extends HigherKinded8<?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,TYPE>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - 1st component type of the type to be constructed
    T2 - 2nd component type of the type to be constructed
    T3 - 3rd component type of the type to be constructed
    T4 - 4th component type of the type to be constructed
    T5 - 5th component type of the type to be constructed
    T6 - 6th component type of the type to be constructed
    T7 - 7th component type of the type to be constructed
    T8 - 8th component type of the type to be constructed
    TYPE - the container type, i.e. the type to be constructed.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Monad8<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,T8,M>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Tuple8

    public interface HigherKinded8<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,T8,TYPE extends HigherKinded8<?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,TYPE>>

    The HigherKinded8 type declares a generic type constructor, which consists of 8 inner/component types and one outer/container type.

    HigherKinded8 is used to approximately simulate higher-kinded/higher-order types, which cannot be expressed with Java.

    Example: Tuple8 implements HigherKind8 in order to override Monad8.flatMap(javaslang.Function8).

    See also
    • Generics of a Higher Kind (Moors, Piessens, Odersky)
    • Kind (type theory) (wikipedia)
    • Type constructor (wikipedia)
    Since:
    1.1.0
